The paper deals with the design and implementation of a fully automated system to rank online news sources based on various factors such as peer reputation, reporting bias, financial pressure, and popularity. The paper also proposes new computational methods for measuring influence and bottomline pressure, and analyzes the effect of media source bias and significance. Given these aspects, the most likely sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper deals with collecting and analyzing large amounts of data from online news sources. Other likely sub-categories include Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as the paper analyzes the citation graph of news reporting, Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC) as the paper studies the effect of media source bias, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as the paper deals with analyzing news content, and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as the paper identifies social bots and aggressive advertisements.
